46. The standard free energy change is $\Delta G_{298}^{\circ}=-R T \ln K=4.84 \mathrm{~kJ} / \mathrm{mol}$. When reactants and products are in their standard states ( 1 bar or 1 atm ), $Q=1$. As the reaction proceeds toward equilibrium, the reaction shifts left (the amount of products drops while the amount of reactants increases): $Q<1$, and $\Delta G_{298}$ becomes less positive as it approaches zero. At equilibrium, $Q=K$, and $\Delta G=0$.
